rComments: Professor Blair is entertaining, but fails to empathize for her students. The midterms and exams are so hard and precise, yet there is no room from improvement. I regret taking her class, and wish teacher's such as Professor Blair cared more about their students individual needs rather than making it impossible to pass and offering no help.

While professor Blair is quite kind, I do not believe that she gives students the proper tools for success. Her feedback on assignments is also quite negative; she emphasizes everything that was done wrong and does not highlight what was well done. Questions for exams are also incredibly specific, making them very difficult to respond to.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Prof. Blair is genuinely one of the most inspiring professors I've ever had the pleasure of having. She will single-handedly reinvigorate your intellectual interests and motivate you to live up to your full academic potential. I had low expectations given the negative reviews on here, but I was completely blown away by how much I enjoyed her class.

Prof Blair is well-spoken and inspiringly intelligent. Her seminar class helped me refine my analytical/presentation skills, but not for free. There was loads of homework counting towards my participation grade, and a TON of (difficult) reading: critical theory articles, numerous novels, etc, so the workload was a little higher than most classes.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Participation matters']

rComments: Such a wonderful and caring prof!! Her lectures are very informative. Theres a lot of readings, but its an English course so that should be expected.

'So like, um'. Constantly. Those three words will mean nothing to you by the time your first lecture is done. I appreciate that she;s trying to be casual, but it makes things difficult. Is not clear on expectations and despite an obsession with punctuality and being ready I find I'm frequently waiting on her to be ready.

I am obsessed with this prof. Her lectures are so interesting and she really cares about students and creates such a warm environment in her classroom. Also incredibly knowledgeable in the field but makes the content accessible and is a fair grader who wants her students to succeed. Absolutely amazing prof.

Despite being very well informed on her subject, Proffesor Blair is very scattered in her lectures. She constantly  jumps from topic to topic and looses track of her lectures. She is always saying things like "kind of", "sort of", "do you know what I mea?" Which is confusing and almost impossible when taking notes.

On the first day, she told us to remember to "make time to think our thoughts" because they're important, and two months later she told us which Audre Lorde poem prompted her to come out. Tbh I'm in love with her.  Highly recommend. (Also a SUPER smart and engaging prof, which is probably more important to know here.)

Jen Blair genuinely cares about the success of her students. She provides interesting, exciting, and novel analyses for the texts in her classes, and supports alternative readings. Her classes extend beyond English proper and often integrate theoretical frameworks belonging to cultural analysis. Best (and kindest) English professor in the faculty.

Professor Blair is the kind of prof you wish you had for every class, your whole degree. Very interesting classes, , clear expectations and best of all she is very supportive and helpful to her students. She genuinely cares about her students and her classes are very welcoming and open, you actually have a connection to your class.

Professor Blair is that rare professor who is both incredibly intelligent while being intellectually generous to her students. She takes great care in creating comfortable learning environments, and providing everyone with the space and opportunity to participate. Her readings of texts are engaging and current. Definitely would recommend!

It's evident that she cares about her students and is passionate about her lectures but they can be hard to follow (um.. like..) and she tends to ramble so it can be difficult to take good notes. Expectations weren't very clear and lectures that were supposed to be from 7-10 could go on until close to 10:15 so everyone loses interest in the end.

Great prof and a great lecturer. She really cares about people putting in an effort and trying to contribute.  Also, there was a book I was unable to afford for the class, and she simply lent me her copy without question. She's the type that wants her students to have every possible opportunity to do well.  Plus we got to go see a play.

She's a young and energetic prof who tries very hard to make the readings accessible and clearly wants to see her students succeed. Her standards can be a bit exacting, but she is always willing to give you extra help during office hours.
This professor works hard to engage her students.  I learned a lot and I hope to take more courses with her in the future!
Unlike many professors, she actually cares about her students. If you seek her help when needed you will definitely get a good grade.
Terrible speaker. Incoherent and vague. "So", "Like", "Sort of", "Kind of, " Know what I mean?" , "Right?" " So like".   It is very difficult to follow her and take notes.
avoid this prof; she does not engage students in lecture and does not like to be interrupted with relevant questions during lecture.
Not the worst.

I love Professor Blair! Yes she is a very hard marker and expects a lot, but if you make the effort to see her outside of class and discuss your work you should have no problem getting a higher grade. She is an extremely intelligent woman, you can learn a LOT from her. I recommend her for sure.

I enjoyed Dr. Blair's class very much. She is very knowledgeable in her subject area and in Literature as a whole. She is very helpful towards students.Wonderful professor and passionate a bout her work. Speak and contribute in class..after all isn't that what we're there for?  Kudos to Dr Blair for being such a young and inspirational teacher

Wonderful professor with a love for Canadian literature. Very enthusiastic and knowledgeable about what she is teaching, makes you feel excited about the material as well. Reasonable amount of reading. Great feedback on essays. Loves to have students visit during office hours. Fantastic class! Recommended to everyone!
Fantastic prof with genuine interest in what she's teaching. Lots of feedback, open to new perspectives. Was the best course I took this year.

She offered me advise and then criticized my paper when I followed her advise. She is big on participation. The reading is pretty light but overall she just could not grasp my attention the way other profs do. I got an average grade to go with my average experience.

Very passionate about Canadian lit, and really got the class engaged.  She's young, energetic, and really knows her stuff. The only class this year that I thoroughly enjoyed and wanted to work hard in. Very stimulating. She leaves detailed comments on essays. Class is both serious and fun.  Only complaint: she's big on participation.
